The paper discusses a deep learning model for a picking robot, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The model uses feature vectors from an intermediate layer of a neural network for few-shot classification, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses multi-task learning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY).
